      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. so if the lactate is being converted back to glucose in the liver, does that mean it's basically just a cycle? and does anything else happen in the muscle itself to prevent the buildup from getting too high during the actual workout?",
      "source": "evaluator"
